{
  "feature_id": "introduce-workspacecontext-interface",
  "phase": "impl",
  "current_round": 2,
  "status": "has_open_high",
  "max_finding_id": 5,
  "findings": [
    {
      "id": "R1-F01",
      "severity": "high",
      "category": "correctness",
      "file": "src/bin/specflow-run.ts",
      "title": "`specflow-run start` still fails through the old git-root path before WorkspaceContext is injected",
      "detail": "`main()` still calls `projectRoot()` before dispatching subcommands. Outside a git repo, `specflow-run start` exits with stderr `Error: not inside a git repository` instead of the required stdout JSON `{\"status\":\"error\",\"error\":\"not_in_git_repo\"}`. This breaks Acceptance Criteria 5/6 and task 3.4/7.14. Fix by dispatching `start` before any raw git lookup, constructing `WorkspaceContext` first, and deriving the root/workflow/store paths from `ctx.projectRoot()`. Add an integration test for `specflow-run start` in a non-git directory.",
      "origin_round": 1,
      "latest_round": 1,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": "",
      "resolved_round": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "R1-F02",
      "severity": "high",
      "category": "correctness",
      "file": "src/bin/specflow-filter-diff.ts",
      "title": "CLI pathspec filtering regressed",
      "detail": "The new arg handling only extracts `:(exclude)...` entries and ignores all other pathspecs. That breaks the documented interface `specflow-filter-diff [-- <pathspec>...]`: for example, `specflow-filter-diff -- sub` now returns diffs for files outside `sub/` as well. This violates the no-breaking-change requirement and diff parity. Preserve non-exclude pathspecs and pass them through to diff selection, or explicitly reject unsupported args after updating the spec. Add a regression test covering an include pathspec.",
      "origin_round": 1,
      "latest_round": 1,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": "",
      "resolved_round": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "R1-F03",
      "severity": "medium",
      "category": "error_handling",
      "file": "src/lib/local-workspace-context.ts",
      "title": "Invalid exclude-pattern warnings are lost on empty diffs",
      "detail": "Before this refactor, `specflow-filter-diff` preserved `DIFF_EXCLUDE_PATTERNS` validation warnings even when there were no changes. Now `filteredDiff()` collapses all no-change cases to `summary: \"empty\"`, and the CLI synthesizes `warnings: []`, so `DIFF_EXCLUDE_PATTERNS='[' specflow-filter-diff` silently drops the invalid-pattern warning. That changes user-input error handling and violates the parity requirement for warning behavior. Return warnings alongside the empty result or have the CLI preserve the old warning-generation path. Add a test for invalid `DIFF_EXCLUDE_PATTERNS` with no repo changes.",
      "origin_round": 1,
      "latest_round": 1,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": "",
      "resolved_round": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "R1-F04",
      "severity": "low",
      "category": "scope",
      "file": "openspec/config.yaml",
      "title": "Unrelated runtime config change is bundled into the WorkspaceContext work",
      "detail": "Adding `max_autofix_rounds: 6` changes repository behavior but is not described anywhere in the WorkspaceContext proposal. It should be removed from this diff or split into a separate spec/change so the implementation stays within scope.",
      "origin_round": 1,
      "latest_round": 1,
      "status": "resolved",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": "",
      "resolved_round": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "R2-F05",
      "severity": "high",
      "category": "correctness",
      "file": "src/bin/specflow-review-apply.ts",
      "title": "Apply review no longer skips excluded-only diffs",
      "detail": "The old `diffFilter()` treated an empty patch body from `specflow-filter-diff` as `no_changes`, so apply review skipped when the worktree contained only deleted files / pure renames / other filtered-out tracked entries. After switching to `ctx.filteredDiff(...)`, `runReviewPipeline()` only short-circuits on `summary === \"empty\"`. For a deleted-file-only change, `filteredDiff()` returns `diff: \"\"` with a non-empty summary, so `specflow-review-apply review` now calls the reviewer on an empty diff and can write a success ledger/current-phase update even though there are no reviewable changes. Restore the old behavior by treating `rawDiff.diff === \"\"` as `no_changes` (or normalizing that case inside `diffFilter()`), and add a regression test for an excluded-only diff such as a deleted file.",
      "origin_round": 2,
      "latest_round": 2,
      "status": "new",
      "relation": "new",
      "supersedes": null,
      "notes": ""
    }
  ],
